INSERT INTO `objects` VALUES (4,1,'2020-03-04 11:38:06','2020-05-07 15:49:17',NULL,'Events  ',NULL,'events',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<center>\r\n<h3><br></h3></center>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"(url)\">Upcoming</a><br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"(url)\">Archive</a><br>',NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL),(10,1,'2020-03-04 11:55:25','2020-05-07 15:30:43',100,'Archive ',NULL,'archive',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'',NULL,NULL,NULL),(27,1,'2020-03-22 13:46:30','2020-05-07 15:21:30',5,'Resource',NULL,'resource',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(215,1,'2020-04-03 15:30:49','2020-05-06 23:24:12',NULL,'Upcoming',NULL,'upcoming',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(285,0,'2020-04-03 19:56:20','2020-04-28 13:18:10',NULL,'About',NULL,'about',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<div class=\"content_section\"><div></div></div>',NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '<div>Trigger is a non-profit academic community devoted to producing content and raising issues in the context of contemporary art. It involves art students, artists, and a halo of interested parties with similar education backgrounds in the United States. Setting up event venues and networking devices in multiple art schools (RISD, Parsons, SVA, VCU, SAIC, NYU), Trigger breaks through geographical restrictions and thus allows art critique workshops, artist talks and panel discussions to take place in multiple spaces simultaneously. Participants of Trigger’s current events are mainly Chinese.</div><h4 class=\"subtitle\">Events</h4><div><ol><li>Each week, Trigger invites two mid-career artists active in the contemporary art circles of China and the United States, respectively, to have online conversations. The event will be live streamed and displayed in multiple art schools mentioned above. At each event site, there is a student helper in charge of debugging Internet devices, coordinating Q &amp; A sessions and offline discussion. Trigger pairs up artists whose works share similar thematic concerns or material approach. While creating more space for interdisciplinary discussion, Trigger aims to deepen its audience’s understanding of various media languages. The conversation between the two artists will be transcribed to textual records and posted online.</li><li>Each Semester, Trigger organizes ten-hour critique “marathon” twice. Students who join the critique workshop voluntarily will present their recent projects and ask other participants for their feedback.</li></ol></div><h4 class=\"subtitle\">Mission</h4><div>Trigger uses an online platform to build an academic community consisting of members from different art schools. By organizing a series of events including artist sharings, panel discussions and exhibitions, Trigger aims to overcome the cultural barrier caused by the language difference and geographical distance between Chinese artists and American audiences. Through interdisciplinary communication, Trigger inspires its participants to explore various methods of artistic research and art-making.</div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<div class=\"content_section\"><div></div></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL),(289,0,'2020-04-10 20:18:25','2020-05-05 15:09:36',NULL,'Cole Lu + Na Buqi',NULL,'kong-mo-cheng-xinhao',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '\r\n<!DOCTYPE html>\r\n<html class=\"\r\n\r\n\">\r\n    <head>\r\n                        <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=utf-8\">\r\n<meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\r\n<meta name=\"color-scheme\" content=\"light dark\">\r\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1.0,maximum-scale=1.0,user-scalable=0,viewport-fit=cover\">\r\n<link rel=\"shortcut icon\" type=\"image/x-icon\" href=\"//res.wx.qq.com/a/wx_fe