Screening List:</h3>\r\n<i>《The History of United Fronts》(HMS Tamar)  《The History of Riots》(The DJ)  《The Narrow Road to the Deep Sea》通向深海的狭道</i>\r\n</center>',NULL,'2020-04-24 00:00:00','Zoom online meeting','Artist Panel Talk  Screening',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'//www.trigggggggger.com/media/00039.png',NULL,NULL),(291,1,'2020-04-10 20:23:11','2020-05-02 11:19:48',NULL,'Melanie Hoff + Lin Ke',NULL,'melanie-hoff-lin-ke',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'2020-05-01 00:00:00','list 2','Artist Panel Talk',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(330,1,'2020-04-28 13:08:57','2020-05-04 21:04:59',10,'Artist Index',NULL,'artist-index',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(331,1,'2020-04-28 13:18:20','2020-05-07 14:52:11',15,'About',NULL,'about',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<div>Mission<br><i>Trigger</i>&nbsp;uses an online platform to build an academic community consisting of members from different art schools. By organizing a series of events including artist sharings, panel discussions and exhibitions,&nbsp;<i>Trigger</i>&nbsp;aims to overcome the cultural barrier caused by the language difference and geographical distance between Chinese artists and American audiences. Through interdisciplinary communication,&nbsp;<i>Trigger</i>&nbsp;inspires its participants to explore various methods of artistic research and art-making.</div><div><br></div><div><div style=\"width: 496.859px;\"><br></div></div>',NULL,NULL,'<br>',NULL,'0000-00-00 00:00:00',_binary '<div>Intro</div> <i>Trigger</i> is a non-profit academic community devoted to producing content and raising issues in the context of contemporary art. It involves art students, artists, and a halo of interested parties with similar education backgrounds in the United States. Setting up event venues and networking devices in multiple art schools, <i>Trigger</i> breaks through geographical restrictions and thus allows <u>art critique workshops, artist talks and panel discussions</u> to take place in multiple spaces simultaneously. Participants of <i>Trigge</i>r’s current events are mainly Chinese.&nbsp;<div><br></div><div>Participating schools includes RISD, Parsons, MICA, SVA, VCU, SAIC and NYU.<h5><br></h5></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL),(332,0,'2020-04-28 17:44:12','2020-05-03 01:41:56',NULL,'Tianzhuo Chen',NULL,'tianzhuo-chen',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Tianzhuo Chen’s practices encompass performance, photography, installations, video and painting. Focusing on the participatory aspects of his works, the results of his works become ritualistic collaborations between the audience and himself. Chen utilizes “elements and symbols found in religion, subculture, pop culture and dance”, with the intend to transcend beyond “the superficial states of the body and spirit”.(k11artfoundation) His strong, unique visual languages enable his practices to push against any previously established parameters.&nbsp;<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" href = \"http://tianzhuochen.com/\">website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(333,1,'2020-04-28 20:10:56','2020-05-05 00:12:26',NULL,'Hsu Che-Yu',NULL,'hsu-che-yu',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/hsu_cheyu85/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Hsu Che-Yu is an visual artist based in Taipei. He earned his master degree from the Graduate Institute of Plastic Arts, Tainan National University of the Arts.&nbsp;Hsu’s artistic practices utilize animation, video and installation to explore how memories are being perceived. He has a special interest in the reconstruction of past memories and events, whether is intimate moments or collective&nbsp;histories. Hsu’s videos illustrate our process of identifying our surroundings through interpretations of memories.<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://https://thisisanapple.blogspot.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(335,1,'2020-04-29 13:22:18','2020-05-05 00:15:29',NULL,'Ni Youyu',NULL,'ni-youyu',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/ni_youyu/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Ni Youyu is a shanghai based multidisciplinary artist. “Viewing Ni Youyu’s work often leaves one with a spatial and temporal illusion.” Most of his art making process requires significant duration and and “go through a degree of uncertainty from gestation to completion.” His works are sometimes positioned apart from the realm of “contemporary art”, as the manner of artisans is deeply embed in his process.The nature of Ni’s works makes it hard for him to “produce works according to an exhibition theme in the manner of a modern artist.” (Perrotin New York)<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"<a class = reference_link href = https://www.niyouyu.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(336,1,'2020-04-29 13:52:10','2020-05-04 23:58:57',NULL,'Lu Pingyuan',NULL,'pingyuanlu',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Lu Pingyuan lives and works in Shanghai. His works have specific interests in texts and fictional writings. Lu incorporates huge amount of nonlinear fictional stories into his practices, and text is considered one of his most frequently used medium. The unexpected, bizarre, and surrealistic writings of Lu provide viewers a glimpse into his contracted context. The writings challenge the boundaries between fantasies and physical realities, redefine the possible state of being of an artwork.<br>',NULL,'<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"https://www.instagram.com/pingyuanlu/\">Instagram</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(337,1,'2020-04-29 13:54:47','2020-05-03 01:56:55',NULL,'Su Jiehao ',NULL,'jiehao-su',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Jiehao Su is an artists working primarily with photography, video, text, and spatial installation. He was born in Guangdong, China and now based in Rhode Island. “He is particularly interested in the poetics and politics of everyday situations, the mediated reality in contemporary society, as well as the physical and metaphysical aspects of the world.”&nbsp;(<a href=\"http://jiehaosu.com\">jiehaosu.com</a>) Su’s practices employ an cinematic approach to explore “the notions of temporality and spatiality in the structure of narrative.”<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"<a class = reference_link href = https://jiehaosu.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(338,1,'2020-04-29 13:55:33','2020-05-03 01:45:01',NULL,'Peng Ke',NULL,'ke-peng',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Ke peng is a Los Angeles based photographer. She was born in Changsha and received her BFA in photography from Rhode Island School of Design. Ke’s works pay close attentions to the subtle connections between things, with an septic focus on the “distinctions within similarity”.<br>Her recent works explore the “colourful corners of China’s smaller cities”, (British Journal of Photography) feature a distinctive approach to observe those overly repetitive, familiar spaces.<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://pengke.studio/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(339,1,'2020-04-29 13:56:05','2020-04-29 13:56:05',NULL,'Mountain River Jump!',NULL,'mountain-river-jump',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '“Mountain River Jump! is an artist duo founded in 2016 by twin sisters Huang Shan and Huang He, who were born in 1985. The duo has a variety of creative formats in art, often applying \"divination consulting\" as a performance to examine the potential of such art medium, and to interact with the audience at the intrinsic level. With their studies into Oriental mysticism and folklore, the artists pry open the topics of identity politics, labor issues, feminism, life politics, modernity and others. They pay attention to the embodiment of mythological clues in a daily context, attempting to carry out \"psychoanalysis\" of the reality, and reflecting on the materialist culture within modern China and its psychological status. Huang Shan and Huang He presently works and lives in Foshan, Guangdong.” (yellowriver1985.com)<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(340,1,'2020-04-29 13:57:07','2020-04-29 13:57:07',NULL,'Tao Hui',NULL,'tao-hui',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Tao Hui lives and works in Beijing. He graduated from Sichuan Academy of Art with a painting degrees and now works as an installation based artist.&nbsp; Tao Hui’s video works draw inspirations from both personal memories and cultural characteristics (TV series, comedy shows and&nbsp; folklores),&nbsp; illustrates our processes of self-identification under constructed narrations. His prattles covers a variety of topic social identity. cultural crisis and&nbsp; gender identity. Tao’s self-established narratives are metaphorically relate to the cultural context of contemporary societies. The absurdities in his works are employed in a provocative manner.&nbsp;<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(341,1,'2020-04-29 13:57:58','2020-05-05 00:18:40',NULL,'Aaajiao',NULL,'aaajiao',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/aaajiao/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,'<br>',NULL,NULL,_binary '“Active online as a media artist, blogger, activist and programmer, aaajiao is the virtual persona of Shanghai- and Berlin- artist Xu Wenkai. Born in 1984—the title of George Orwell’s classic allegorical novel— and in one of China’s oldest cities, Xi’an, aaajiao’s art and works are marked by a strong dystopian awareness, literati spirits and sophistication. Many of aaajiao’s works speak to new thinkings, controversies and phenomenon around the Internet, with specific projects focusing on the processing of data, the blogsphere and China’s Great Fire Wall.” (<a href=\"https://eventstructure.com/aaajiao\">https://eventstructure.com/aaajiao</a>)<br><figure class=\"img_ctner\"><br><figcaption></figcaption></figure>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"https://www.eventstructure.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,'//www.trigggggggger.com/media/00024.jpg',NULL,NULL),(342,1,'2020-04-29 13:58:20','2020-05-07 00:28:37',NULL,'Guan Xiao',NULL,'guan-xiao',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Guan Xiao’s practices involve sculptures and video arts. She currently works in Beijing.&nbsp;<br>Her works actively explores cultural histories to identify their impacts on contemporary cultures, serving as a juxtaposition of the past and future. Guan’s sculptures pay close attentions to forms and materials that resembles life,&nbsp; including animal shells, scales and plant roots. “Her comparisons of regionally and chronologically disparate objects expose similarities among civilizations, regions, and eras while avoiding solid conclusions.”(<a href=\"http://artsy.net\">artsy.net</a>) Humors and resistances are well-integrated into her explorations.<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(343,1,'2020-04-29 13:58:37','2020-04-29 13:58:37',NULL,'Yang Jian',NULL,'yang-jian',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Yang Jian is a curator and artist works based in Beijing. His practices encompass installation, video and performance. Yang casts doubts on the mundane everyday objects to speak against their functionalities. Contradictory and absurd statements&nbsp; are made out of his unexpected combinations of materials. The unplanned metaphors embodied in his sculptures speak aginst the established everyday logics. His works, embrace a calm and poetic manner, detach the chosen objects from their original cultural context.&nbsp;<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(344,1,'2020-04-29 13:58:54','2020-05-04 22:27:11',NULL,'Zhao Zhao',NULL,'zhao-zhao',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '“Zhao Zhao was born in Xinjiang, China, in 1982. He graduated with a BFA from the Xinjiang Institute of Arts from the department of Oil Painting in 2003. Zhao Zhao’s multidisciplinary body of work is an inspection of China’s contemporary profile, and the socio-political consequences of individual human action. His abstract shattered glass paintings reveal a car accident he was involved in, and represents the ripple effect of action; his “Safe” sculptures substantiate his fellow citizens’ paranoid views on security.” (Chambers Fine Art) With confronting and bold commentaries on politics, His works challenges the traditions of social norms, indicates his unique opinions on Anarchism and anti-authoritarian.<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://www.zhaoyao.org/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(345,1,'2020-04-29 13:59:13','2020-04-29 13:59:13',NULL,'Guo Cheng',NULL,'guo-cheng',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Guo Cheng has a background of industrial and product design, currently lives and works in Shanghai. His art practices encompass installation, video and performance. Guo’s works examine the influences of booming technologies on our social and cultural awarenesses, as well as social interactions of individuals. Constructed machineries are important component of Guo’s installation. His works propose fictional imaginations of body extensions, in order to interpret how technologies cast influence on our day to day life.&nbsp;<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(346,1,'2020-04-29 13:59:35','2020-05-03 01:49:24',NULL,'Li Weiyi ',NULL,'weiyi-li',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '“Weiyi Li is an artist weiyi.li, designer weiyiandfriends.com, curator bigbadgallery.com, publisher re-publication.com and retailor currently-available.com who lives and works between these five URLs.”(wiyi.li) Li has a text-based approach with her art practices. Her works re-interpret the collected texts and daily objects and reassign them to the viewers. The original functionalities of those chosen objects are altered by artist\'s objective understandings, which lead to intriguing associations.<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"https://weiyi.li/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(347,1,'2020-04-29 14:00:09','2020-05-03 01:56:42',NULL,'Luka Yuanyuan Yang',NULL,'luka-yuanyuan-yang',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '“ Luka Yuanyuan Yang graduated from London College of Communications, University of the Arts London with a BA (hons) in photography. She currently lives and works in Beijing, San Francisco or New York. Most of the time, Luka Yuanyuan Yang’s projects take the research and collected historical materials as the departure, and they evolve along with individual experiences relate to specific places. By creating narratives where facts and fiction coexist, she challenges the rigid and conventional interpretation of history and gives voices to subjects that have been forgotten, silenced, and misinterpreted. Yang creates visual narrative through photography, writings, video, artist books and performance.<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"<a class = reference_link href = ocula.com\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(348,1,'2020-04-29 14:00:36','2020-04-29 14:00:36',NULL,'Shen Xin',NULL,'shen-xin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Shen Xin lives and works in London and Amsterdam. “ Through images and events, Shen explores emotions, value judgements and ethics that circulate through individual and collective subjects.” (k11artfoundation) Her recent project explores Buddhism under the context of western communities, with specific focus on the existing conflicts between Buddhism beliefs and&nbsp;patriarchal&nbsp;societies.<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(356,1,'2020-05-03 01:38:10','2020-05-03 12:43:17',NULL,'Chen Tianzhuo',NULL,'chen-tianzhuo',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Tianzhuo Chen’s practices encompass performance, photography, installations, video and painting. Focusing on the participatory aspects of his works, the results of his works become ritualistic collaborations between the audience and himself. Chen utilizes “elements and symbols found in religion, subculture, pop culture and dance”, with the intend to transcend beyond “the superficial states of the body and spirit”(k11artfoundation) His strong, unique visual languages enable his practices to push against any previously established parameters.&nbsp;<br><div><br></div>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://tianzhuochen.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(357,1,'2020-05-03 01:51:00','2020-05-03 01:51:00',NULL,'Hao Jingban',NULL,'hao-jingban',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '“Hao Jingban works with film and video to investigate the historical distance between the present viewer and a certain era in the past. In her research-based practice, the artist conducts historical investigation, archival research, field study, personal interviews, and live performances. From the ballroom dancing in Beijing before and after the Cultural Revolution, to the films of North-eastern China from the 1930s, the artist weaves together complex historical narratives, social movements and cultural commentary against the ambivalence and silence of the bygone era.” (Blindspot Gallery)&nbsp;<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(358,1,'2020-05-03 01:52:26','2020-05-03 01:52:26',NULL,'Wang Xin',NULL,'wang-xin',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Wang Xin&nbsp;is both an art historian and curator based in New York. She’s currently pushing her PhD degrees in modern and contemporary art history at NYU. She\'s currently building a discursive archive of Asian Futurisms at afuturism.tumblr.com. “Past curatorial projects include Ink Art: Past as Present in Contemporary China, Metropolitan Museum of Art (2013, New York), Field Meeting of Asian Contemporary Art Week (2014, New York), artist Lu Yang’s solo debut in New York: Arcade (2014, New York), THE BANK SHOW: Vive le Capital and THE BANK SHOW: Hito Steyerl (2015, Shanghai), chin(A)frica: an interface (2017, New York), and Life and Dreams: Photography and Media Art in China since the 1990s (2018, Ulm, Germany).” (blancdexin.com)&nbsp;<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"https://blancdexin.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(359,1,'2020-05-03 01:54:04','2020-05-03 01:54:04',NULL,'Wang Huan',NULL,'wang-huan',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '“Wang Huan is a Beijing-based Writer, Curator and Editor of <i>Jiazazhi Magazine</i>. He has published a series of art reviews in <i>LEAP Magazine</i>, <i>Art World Magazine</i>, <i>Jiazazhi Magazine</i>, <i>Art Shard </i>and <i>Ray Art Center</i>’<i>s Reviews. </i>He has recently won Royal College of Art’s International Awards for Art Criticism for an article on Christian Boltanski’s <i>Storage Memory </i>at Power Station of Art, Shanghai. ” (aestheticamagazine.com)&nbsp;<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"https://huan-wang.com/author/renwangfoto/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(361,1,'2020-05-03 01:59:03','2020-05-03 01:59:03',NULL,'Ren Xinyi',NULL,'ren-xinyi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Ren Xinyi is a curator currently lives and works in New York. She has a bachelor degree in Art History from Tsinghua Academy of Arts &amp; Design, and a MFA degree in curatorial practice for the School of Visual Arts. “Her practice is rooted in a fractured existence of constantly migrating between cultures, fed by capricious research into internet culture, paracolonial alliances and unconventional media, and fueled by a curiosity toward alternative/conceptual futures.”(xinyirenxinyi.info)&nbsp;<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"https://xinyirenxinyi.info/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(362,1,'2020-05-03 02:02:50','2020-05-03 02:02:50',NULL,'Qi Zhenzhen',NULL,'qi-zhenzhen',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Qi Zhenzhen works both as an educator and a new media artist.<br>Her practices utilize computational and programming languages to reconstruct systematic visuals. Qi is currently pursuing her PhD degree at Columbia university, to explore the implementation of new media in educational institutes. Her projects aim to build sincere connections with the viewers, whether they are positive or negative, conscious or non-conscious. Qi believes that discussions are valid only through sincere communications.&nbsp;<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://zhenzhenqi.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(363,1,'2020-05-03 02:06:09','2020-05-03 02:06:09',NULL,'Wang Yang ',NULL,'wang-yang',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Yang is a designer, a computational media artist, and a software developer based in Brooklyn, New York. He is the co-founder and Director of Art &amp; Technology of New York-based research &amp; production studio&nbsp;<a href=\"https://powernapstudio.com/\" style=\"background-color: transparent; outline: none; color: var(--color-content-linked, #B8A772);\">Power Nap</a>, Besides creating his own artwork and working with QI Zhenzhen.<br>Throughout Yang’s practice, computation serves as both a tool for art-making, and the subject of study. His work utilizes simulation to recreate conditions for critical examination.<br><br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"https://wangyang.io/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(364,1,'2020-05-03 02:13:12','2020-05-03 02:13:12',NULL,'Ge Yulu',NULL,'ge-yulu',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Ge Yulu was born in 1990 in Wuhan, Hubei. He received a Bachelor’s degree in Visual Media Art from Hubei Institute of Fine Art in 2013, and Master’s degree in Experimental Art from China Central Academy of Fine Arts (CAFA) in 2017. He now works and lives in Beijing and Wuhan. Most of his artworks are about individuals’ resistance in public space. He intends to motivate discussion on related topics by practicing extreme performance, and to evoke the public’s participation by creating interference.(chinafile.com)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(365,1,'2020-05-03 02:15:51','2020-05-03 02:15:51',NULL,'Brother Nut',NULL,'brother-nut',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Brother Nut is an internationally-known performance artist based in Beijing, China. He is known only by his pseudonym, Jian-guo-xiong-di, which is also sometimes translated in English as \"Nut Brother.\" He was born in Shenzhen in 1981. His best known work is 2015\'s \"Project Dust,\" which consisted of the creation of a brick made entirely from particulate matter vacuumed out of heavily polluted Beijing city air. This project spotlighted Beijing\'s ongoing air pollution problems at a time when China sought to recast itself as an environmentally-aware nation. Project Dust received press coverage in the United States and Europe,as well as in Asian press.An online photo gallery is also maintained to summarize the activity of the project. (Wikipedia)',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(366,1,'2020-05-03 02:18:42','2020-05-03 23:12:12',NULL,'Li Boyan',NULL,'li-bojian',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Independent curator. He graduated from the Department of Traditional ChinesePainting, Tianjin Academy of Fine Art in 2006. In the year 2012, he founded the nonprofit art institute Space Regeneration Projects. He was the curator of the public exhibition unit of the Sanxingdui Drama Festival in 2017, the curator of the public space performance unit of the Shenzhen contemporary Theatre Biennale in 2018, and the Experimental Unite of The Seventh Jinan International Biennial. （li-boyan.com）<div><br></div>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"li-boyan.com\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(367,1,'2020-05-03 02:23:11','2020-05-03 02:31:38',NULL,'DEVOLUTION',NULL,'devolution',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '\"DEVOLUTION\", established in 2016 by Tang Jiansong, Wang Qi and Yang Lutong, is a \"3A company\" dedicated to providing comprehensive plans of Architecture, Art and advertisement. \"DEVOLUTION\" is also an open and creative studio that inspires to connect architecture with various media, produces new ideas on architecture and urban living, and hopes to bring architectural thinking and artistic approaches into different areas. （devolution.cn）','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://www.devolution.cn/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(368,1,'2020-05-03 02:34:24','2020-05-05 14:02:20',NULL,'Wu Ziyang',NULL,'wu-ziyang',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/ziyang_wu_art/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Wu Ziyang’s art practice focuses on a new power of control rooted in what he has termed as “post Internet micro-alienation”. Referring to contemporary technology, digital power structures, popular culture, and the alienation of an individual’s spirit and body, he draws on these themes to create works rooted in absurdist and carnivalesque techniques to propose critiques and celebrations of alienated culture. His multimedia installations, 3D animations and interactive media have been exhibited internationally. （NewInc）','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://www.ziyangwu.com/index.html\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(369,1,'2020-05-03 02:41:25','2020-05-05 16:05:51',NULL,'Kong Mo',NULL,'kong-mo',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/mosmosk/\">Instagram</a>\r\n<div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Kong Mo is a multidisciplinary artist, researcher. They are currently residing in Queens, NY. They received MFA from Rhode Island School of Design. Their work always deeply impacted by the social events, coded by the “educational information system” to post questions about the current politic environment. Their research led process usually takes the form of large scale installations involving science research and multiple journalism perspectives in which they challenges key issues of the day using complex narratives that synthesis the past with the present.The systems they build normally merged multiple environmental crisis and social politic issues, through the scientific researching and social investigate, they find the similarity of two systems and bring them to one narrative storyline.&nbsp;<div><br>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p onclick=\"TestsFunction()\"><u><b>Show Feed</b></u></p>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"TestsDiv\" style=\"display:none\">\r\n    <blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-permalink=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/B8Pg4sLFr5O/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" data-instgrm-version=\"12\" style=\" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:540px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);\"><div style=\"padding:16px;\"> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/B8Pg4sLFr5O/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" style=\" background:#FFFFFF; 