NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Pu Yingwei (born 1989 in Shanxi, China) lives and works in Beijing China. Pu Yingwei\'s creation is based on his research of literature and archive, he believes that the individual experience and memory are evidence that one exists in the world. Through different media such as video, installation, photography, painting, and texts, the artists crosses the boundaries of race, country, religion, language, to finally create a perceptual archive and his autobiography. (galeriesator.com)<div><br></div>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://www.puyingwei.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(372,1,'2020-05-03 02:52:43','2020-05-03 02:53:53',NULL,'Xin Liu',NULL,'xin-liu',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Xin Liu (b. 1991, Xinjiang/China) is an artist and engineer, whose works range from performances, apparatus, installations to scientific experiments and academic papers. In her practice, Xin creates experiences and artifacts to measure and modify the distance and tension between personal, social and technological spaces. They are moments of re-organization, creating ripples in the fabric of subjectivities, common experiences and beliefs . (xxxxxxxxxinliu.com)','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"www.xxxxxxxxxinliu.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(373,1,'2020-05-03 02:56:56','2020-05-03 02:56:56',NULL,'Li Xiaofei',NULL,'li-xiaofei',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Li Xiaofei lives and works in Shanghai and New York. His multidisciplinary practices include photography, video, installation and painting. His ongoing project The Assembly Line discusses the rapid social developments through documenting the employees working in various factories. The systematic working environments are addressed to reveal the impacts of consumerism. “For Li Xiaofei, the assembly line represents a repetitive, identical, mechanical and even unemotional means of production, one which efficiently and rapidly expands the value of production to the&nbsp;<br>utmost. Such repetition and sameness do not refer merely to machines but also include the workers living amid all this as well as the final products.” (lixiaofei.org)&nbsp;<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"lixiaofei.org\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(374,1,'2020-05-03 02:57:34','2020-05-03 02:57:34',NULL,'Lee Mingwei',NULL,'lee-mingwei',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary '“Born in Taiwan in 1964 and currently living in Paris and New York City, Lee Mingwei creates participatory installations, where strangers can explore issues of trust, intimacy, and self- awareness, and one-on-one events, where visitors contemplate these issues with the artist through eating, sleeping, walking and conversation. Lee\'s projects are often open-ended scenarios for everyday interaction, and take on different forms with the involvement of participants and change during the course of an exhibition.”(leemingwei.com)&nbsp;<br>','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"leemingwei.com\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(375,1,'2020-05-03 02:58:09','2020-05-03 02:58:09',NULL,'Lu Mingjun',NULL,'lu-mingjun',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Lu Mingjun is a historian, curator and art critic, and the associate professor at Sichuan University School of the Arts. His researches mainly focus on the history of modern and contemporary art. “His thesis was found in Literature &amp; Art Studies, Art Studies, 21st Century, Artforum,Leap, etc..His recent books include Writing and Narrating of Vision: The Vision of History and Theory (2013); Visual Cognition and Art History: Michel Foucault, Hubert Damisch, Jonathan Crary (2014); and On Meta-Painting: An Art Institution and Cognition of Universality (2015).” (Tang Contemporary Art)&nbsp;<br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(376,1,'2020-05-03 23:18:52','2020-05-03 23:18:52',NULL,'Wang Xu',NULL,'wang-xu',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'list 2',NULL,NULL,_binary 'Born in Dalian, China, Xu Wang works in sculpture, video installation, drawing, and performance. Interested in process and materiality, Wang continues to explore a series that re-contextualizes found and collected objects and matter. He received his BFA from the China Central Academy of Fine Arts and MFA from Columbia University. He has exhibited internationally at Galerist Gallery (Turkey), Queens Museum (New York), SculptureCenter (New York), among others. （pioneerworks.org）','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"https://www.wang-xu.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(378,1,'2020-05-04 21:04:46','2020-05-05 00:13:52',NULL,'Lin Aojie',NULL,'lin-aojie',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/lin_aojie/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Aojie Lin currently lives and works in Guangzhou. Most of his works&nbsp; draw inspirations from the mundane every experiences. Lin’s practices involve video, photography, drawing and text, feature acute sensibilities towards spontaneities and humors. Lin’s works are provocative in a sense that they covers concerns relating “the disjuncture between art and capitalism, annoyance with an artist’s social responsibilities, even frustration with his own ambition.” (ArtAisaPacific) His voice are expressed through mockery of those daily narrations.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(379,0,'2020-05-04 21:09:07','2020-05-04 21:09:30',NULL,'testtesttest',NULL,'testtesttest',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(380,0,'2020-05-04 21:11:32','2020-05-04 21:11:53',NULL,'ee',NULL,'ee',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(381,1,'2020-05-04 21:15:49','2020-05-05 00:09:26',NULL,'Chen Xinhao',NULL,'chen-xinhao',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/chengxinhaodeab/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Chen Xinhao was&nbsp;born in Yunnan(China) in1985. He received his Ph.D. in Chemistry from Peking University in 2013. He is working as an artist in Yunnan now.<br style=\"color: rgb(38, 38, 38); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">With videos, installations, and article writing, his works investigate the issue in the modernization, the construction of knowledge as well as the production of space in Chinese society. He also adopts his body as a medium to build the connection between personal effect and specific historical narrative s and places.','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://chengxinhao.me/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(382,1,'2020-05-04 21:32:52','2020-05-04 21:33:25',NULL,'Zhang Ruyi',NULL,'zhang-ruyi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Zhang Ruyi\'s&nbsp;artistic practice embeds itself is nothing less than the logic of life. It is centered on the undisclosed relationship between ego-consciousness, physical space, and mundane experience. By withholding certain ‘slices’ of time and information of the material employed, the artist is able to capture, replicate, compress, condense, or fabricate the materialization of emotions. She is dedicated to the exploration of both positive and negative frictions between individuals and reality, nature, and industrial landscape. Its position is that of a discursive apparatus, transforming the tactile into the visual. Taking the relational language of order aesthetics, she suggests the reconstruction of a specific space to be ‘read,’ ‘questioned,’ and ‘memorized.’ She employs objects to question objects and spaces to question spaces, thus resisting the order.','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://www.zhangruyi.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(383,1,'2020-05-04 21:36:17','2020-05-05 00:17:19',NULL,'William Lamson',NULL,'williamlamson',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/williamlamson/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'William Lamson is an interdisciplinary artist whose diverse practice involves working with elemental forces to create durational performative actions. Set in landscapes as varied as New York’s East River and Chile’s Atacama Desert, his projects reveal the invisible systems and forces at play within these sites. In all of his projects, Lamson’s work represents a performative gesture, a collaboration with forces outside of his control to explore systems of knowledge and belief.','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://www.williamlamson.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(384,1,'2020-05-04 21:37:59','2020-05-05 00:11:28',NULL,'Corin Hewitt',NULL,'corin-hewitt',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/corinhewitt/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Corin Hewitt lives and works in Richmond, VA. He employs photography, video, performance, installation, and sculpture in an ongoing investigation of objects and images as active and evolving events. His process centered approach engages both human and non-human systems in order to explore their transformative effects.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(385,1,'2020-05-04 21:40:10','2020-05-05 00:17:46',NULL,'Zhao Yao',NULL,'zhaoxao',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/zhaoxao/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Zhao Yao&nbsp;is good at using the material\'s changing process in nature to preserve the memory of the place. The artwork places certain memory and spirit in a completely different context by its transforming in space and time. His most recent works (Something in the Air; Spirit is above all; Signals from Heaven, Signals from Heaven), by using the imagination and knowledge of Tibetan Buddhism, mobilizing a large number of social resources, and making the work transformed into a mass public engagement act. Zhao Yao was trying to maximizing the scale and transportation distance of his artworks. In his artworks, he created a kind of imagination of the Tibetan area through comprehensive materials, and on the other hand, showed the manpower expend during the constitution of this spectacle. He always shows a dual attitude of trusting but skeptical about spiritual energy in his work.<br style=\"color: rgb(38, 38, 38); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(386,1,'2020-05-04 21:41:45','2020-05-05 00:08:41',NULL,'Catalina Ouyang',NULL,'catalina-ouyang',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/kittytuna/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Catalina Ouyang\'s practice spans sculpture, language, installation, performance, video, participatory projects, and other modalities to inhabit the interstices of myth, desire, subjugation, and monstrosity. Ouyang holds an MFA from Yale University and is based in New York.','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"https://catalinaouyang.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(387,1,'2020-05-04 21:43:43','2020-05-05 00:16:31',NULL,'Virginia Lee Montgomery',NULL,'skinnyyaliens',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/skinnyaliens/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Virginia Lee Montgomery&nbsp;(b. Houston, TX, USA) is an artist working between Texas and New York, primarily in video, performance, sound, and sculpture. She received her BFA from The University of Texas at Austin in 2008 and her MFA from Yale University in Sculpture in 2016. VLM deploys an idiosyncratic visual vocabulary of repeating gestures like drilling, dousing, or reaching and recursive symbols like circles, holes and spheres as she interrogates the complex relationship between physical and psychic structures. VLM also works as a professional mind-map scribe, a Graphic Facilitator.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(388,1,'2020-05-04 21:44:46','2020-05-04 22:25:16',NULL,'Chang Ting-Tong',NULL,'chang-ting-tong',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Ting-Tong Chang（张硕尹）is a Taiwanese artist based in London. His satirical gaze leaves no aspect of society untouched. Reveling in the absurd and illogical, he makes a mockery of socio-political subjects ranging from the social and ecological effects of consumerism to the functioning of the art world itself.','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://tingtongchang.co.uk/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(389,1,'2020-05-04 21:47:15','2020-05-04 21:47:15',NULL,'Jo Wei ',NULL,'jo-wei',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Jo Wei（魏颖）is a curator and researcher. Her recent research interests include Art,<br style=\"color: rgb(38, 38, 38); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Science and technology in a posthuman context, Bio Art，STS, and others. She is also the founder of the Pan Bio-Art Studio (PBS). Among the list of her many curations are Towards the Emergence of Resistance: The Eye of Representation (2016, Taikang Space, Beijing) and When Forms do not Become Attitude (2016, CAFAM,<br style=\"color: rgb(38, 38, 38); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Beijing). Wei is currently a researcher of Art, Science, and Technology (AST) in the Central Academy of Fine Arts (CAFA) and was the unit curator of Ethics of Technology (2016) and Post-Life (2018), respectively the first and second editions of the Beijing Media Art Biennale. An invited speaker for conferences held at Taipei National University of the Arts, Tsinghua University, the Institute of Neurology of the Chinese Academy of Sciences (CAS), etc., she is also an International Advisor for the European Commission’s 2019 STARTS Prize.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(390,1,'2020-05-04 21:49:13','2020-05-05 00:09:59',NULL,'Chen Yiyun',NULL,'cloud-xs',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/cloud.xs/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Chen Yiyun is a designer/artist currently based in Shanghai. She graduated from MA Design Interactions at the Royal College of Art (London, UK) and obtained a BA in Digital Media Design at Tongji University (Shanghai, China). She holds a diploma of Traditional Chinese Medicine at Shanghai University of TCM.<br style=\"color: rgb(38, 38, 38); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Her practices discuss the relationships between a man and his/her body, interrelation between emerging technologies and individual life, using the language of speculative and critical design. She currently interests in the realms where art and life science connect, concerned with the human wellbeing under the topic of illness and wellness.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(391,1,'2020-05-04 21:52:31','2020-05-05 00:16:07',NULL,'Sydney Shen',NULL,'sydney-shen',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/lawnmowerwoman/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Sydney Shen&nbsp;(b. 1989, Woodbridge, NJ) is an artist who lives and works in NYC. She received BFA from the Cooper Union College in 2011.<br style=\"color: rgb(38, 38, 38); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Her sculptures and installations evoke a sense of abject dread. Informed by a range of historical and contemporary sources—including Peking opera, supernatural horror fiction, and the darkest recesses of the web—Shen frankensteins organic and synthetic materials such as Chinese and Western medicinal aromatics, 3-D-printed plastic, and biological specimens to produce uncanny environments.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(392,1,'2020-05-04 21:54:24','2020-05-05 00:13:18',NULL,'Leung Chi Wo',NULL,'leung-chi-wo',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Leung Chi Wo is a visual artist and co-founder of&nbsp;<a class=\"notranslate\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/parasite.hk/\" style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgba(var(--fe0,0,55,107),1); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">@parasite.hk</a>&nbsp;. His reflective practice combines historical exploration with conceptual inquiry within a contemporary urban landscape. Ranging from photography and video to text, performance and installation, he is concerned with the undetermined relationship between conception, perception and understanding, especially in relation to site and history within cultural/political frameworks. His practice always involves research into different contexts and situations, and the artistic outcomes linked to the hidden relationships of various subjects.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(393,1,'2020-05-04 21:55:41','2020-05-05 00:10:35',NULL,'Christopher K. Ho',NULL,'christopher-k-ho',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/ckh7ckh7/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Christopher K. Ho is a speculative artist based in New York, Hong Kong, and Telluride, Colorado. His practice encompasses making, organizing, writing, and teaching. He is known for materially exquisite objects that draw equally from learned material about and lived encounters with, power and otherness in an unevenly de-colonialized, increasingly networked world.','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://www.artforum.com.cn/interviews/12385/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(394,1,'2020-05-04 21:57:47','2020-05-05 00:15:08',NULL,'Nabuqi',NULL,'nabuqi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/nbqaui/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Nabuqi ( b. 1984 Inner Mongolia, lives Beijing) is deeply committed to exploring the aesthetic and material aspects of sculpted objects; for the artist it is important that the imitation of the outdoors is realised through an assemblage of manufactured objects whose original qualities are faithfully kept: “I wanted to recover the initial state and properties of the materials, instead of compromising these with my own hands. Which means not showing a meticulously created artwork in the exhibition space. I also wanted to construct an environment that pertains to both the outdoor (external) and the interior (internal). All the materials used here are decorative in nature, supposedly simulating or stimulating a kind of reality, or nurturing an imagination of an aesthetics: a virtual aesthetics, pleasant and hospitable”. Can such a recreation of reality be perceived as part of reality, and does it trigger the same emotional resonances in the audience as if they had encountered the real? Her artworks try to answer such questions.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(395,1,'2020-05-04 22:02:24','2020-05-05 00:11:00',NULL,'Cole Lu',NULL,'cole-lu',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/colelu/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Cole Lu (b. Taipei) is an artist and writer based in New York. Lu’s practice implies various literary devices that result in sculpture, installation, text, and video. Through rewriting classical mythology and allegorical science fiction, Lu’s work reflects the collective unconscious and comments on the motif of othering through colonial viewpoints. Each body of work is developed from anecdotal evidence, to question the capacity of historical realism and is part of a lifelong series of the artist’s ‘real fiction’ on contemporary values and belief systems.','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://cole-lu.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(396,1,'2020-05-04 22:04:00','2020-05-05 00:16:55',NULL,'Wang Tuo',NULL,'wang-tuo',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/buddhathugtuo/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Wang Tuo was born and raised in Changchun, China, and currently lives and works in Beijing. Wang Tuo employs various mediums and a process that combined interview, reality show and the theatre of absurd to construct a maze of melodrama. Through his performative manipulation on individuals’ lived experiences and intervention in intellectual legacies such as literature, film, theatre and art history, Wang’s practice attempts to examine the unreliable relationship between the contemporary human status, myth and cultural archive. In the self-referential environments that he constructs, dramatic, often humorous as well as absurd aspects of the concept of society are exposed. Wang’s practice also seeks to develop a discourse on how present ideology is derived from its historical context continues to adapt to changing condition.','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://www.tuo-wang.com\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(397,1,'2020-05-04 22:06:25','2020-05-04 22:10:51',NULL,'Lee Kai Chung',NULL,'lee-kai-chung',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Lee Kai Chung performs research on historical events, political systems, and ideology. His work addresses the lack of proper governance over the records and pending legislation for Archives Law. Through performance, documentation, and installation, Lee considers the individual gesture as a form of political and artistic transgression, which resonates with existing narratives of history. Lee’s ongoing research project “Archive of the People” addresses the political standing of documents and archives in the social setting. In 2016, Lee established collective “Archive of the People”, which serves as an extension of his personal research to collaborative projects, education and publications.','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://http://www.leekaichung.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(398,1,'2020-05-04 22:09:10','2020-05-05 00:14:43',NULL,'Melanie Hoff',NULL,'melanie-hoff',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/melanieh0ff/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Melanie Hoff&nbsp;is an artist and educator examining the role technology plays in social organization and reinforcing hegemonic structures. Their work uncovers coded conventions of norms, interfaces, and sex, through software, installation, and new choreographies of exchange. They are a founding member of the Cybernetics Library, an art and research collective offering resources for study and critique of technosocial systems and Soft Surplus, a collective art studio warehouse for learning together by making things near each other.','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://https://melanie-hoff.com/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(399,1,'2020-05-04 22:13:46','2020-05-05 00:14:14',NULL,'Lin Ke',NULL,'lin-ke',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/linkewaco/\">Instagram</a>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary 'Lin Ke (b. 1984, Wenzhou, China) is an artist based in Shanghai. He graduated from the New Media Art program at China Academy of Art in 2008, and joined&nbsp;<a class=\" xil3i\" href=\"https://www.instagram.com/explore/tags/doubleflyartcenter/\" style=\"border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: inherit; font-variant-east-asian: inherit; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: inherit; font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif; vertical-align: baseline; color: rgba(var(--fe0,0,55,107),1); overflow-wrap: break-word; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);\">#DoubleFlyArtCenter</a>&nbsp;in2014.<br style=\"color: rgb(38, 38, 38); font-family: -apple-system, system-ui, &quot;Segoe UI&quot;, Roboto, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;\">Since 2010, Lin Ke has created a series of videos and pictures related to computer and the Internet. Lin Ke regards his MacBook as a studio, uses the mouse and screen to make improvisations, and records them by software. Sometimes, his MacBook is the stage where he performs in front of the built-in camera. In his works, Lin Ke uses computer software skillfully in an unconventional way to look for new functions beyond the original design intention. He allows the language can be liberated from the basic communication function and gain poetic. If poetry expresses the pleasure of language, Lin Ke\'s work presents the pleasure of the user interface.','<a class = \"reference_link\" target = \"_blank\" href = \"http://vimeo.com/user4187761/\">Website</a><br>',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(400,0,'2020-05-05 00:33:21','2020-05-07 00:28:27',NULL,'Guan Xiao',NULL,'guan-xiao',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '<div><br></div>',NULL,NULL,NULL,'Artist Panel Talk',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'//www.trigggggggger.com/media/00027.jpeg',NULL,NULL),(401,0,'2020-05-05 12:40:08','2020-05-05 12:40:15',NULL,'test',NULL,'test',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(402,0,'2020-05-05 15:07:54','2020-05-06 23:40:21',NULL,'Cole Lu + Na Buqi ææ–™çš„è¡¨è¾¾æ–¹å¼',NULL,'cole-lu-na-buqi',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,_binary '\r\n\r\n\r\n<meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p onclick=\"TestsFunction()\"><u><b>Show Content</b></u></p>\r\n\r\n<div id=\"TestsDiv\" style=\"display:none\">\r\n    <center>\r\n    线上对谈：材料的表达式 | Cole Lu &amp; 娜布其 <br><br><br>\r\n    \r\n    艺术家<br>\r\n    <b><i>Artist_</i></b><br><br><br>  </center>\r\n    <center><img src=\"https://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_jpg/pLhvdZgejGQmYHW1jLw1Yg45ePQSoqMnoo7fibd4THxLQzsoKA5j924GhqZV5vL81wLXAFoOFhibpV1cJicSWXcicg/640?wx_fmt=jpeg&amp;tp=webp&amp;wxfrom=5&amp;wx_lazy=1&amp;wx_co=1\" alt=\"Girl in a jacket\" width=\"400\" height=\"550\"></center><br>\r\n     <font size=\"2\">Cole Lu 艺术家、作家。出生于台北，现居于纽约。其创作通过文字、雕塑、数字影像和混合媒介探索差异性和异化的概念。Lu的作品曾在美国、希腊、德国、英国等多个国家的画廊及美术馆展出。其出版物 Smells Like Content (Endless Editions)被收录于纽约MoMa图书馆艺术家藏书(artists’ book collection of the MoMA Library, New York)。<br>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://cole-lu.com/\">https://cole-lu.com/</a></p><br>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/colelu/\">@colelu</a></p>\r\n\r\n</font>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<center><img src=\"https://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_jpg/pLhvdZgejGQmYHW1jLw1Yg45ePQSoqMnpsSlSdZ1ySIrt5TYQhSedlHGDibHvegj5FdnsCknq6blLARUXQuubVA/640?wx_fmt=jpeg&amp;tp=webp&amp;wxfrom=5&amp;wx_lazy=1&amp;wx_co=1\" width=\"400\" height=\"550\"></center><br>\r\n  <font size=\"2\"><b>娜布其 Nabuqi</b> 1984年出生于中国内蒙古自治区，2013年毕业于中央美术学院，现工作生活于北京。娜布其的作品从对物体的关注开始，延伸至物体和身体的关系以及人在不同空间、环境中感知的不同。物体系列关注物体的独立性本身，与身体形成对照和相互影响的关系。娜布其的作品时常将单件雕塑进行组合，形成在空间中的片段式场景。同时她也将这种思考延伸至更大的范围，尝试探讨在公共空间中人和周围环境的关系等。<br><br>\r\n  近期展览包括“真实发生在事物具有合理性的瞬间吗？” （上海香格里拉画廊，2018），“寒夜”（UCCA艺术中心，2017），“缺失的段落”（Museum Beelden aan Zee，2017），球场（中央美术学院美术馆，2017），第十一届上海双年展（2016），第十一届光州双年展（2016）等。曾入围2016年华宇青年奖。<br>\r\n@nbqaui\r\n</font>\r\n<br><br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<br><br><br><br>\r\n<center>\r\n<b><i>Cole Lu_</i></b><br><br>\r\n<b><i><font size=\"3\">✦ The Dust Enforcer (All These Darlings Said It’s the End and Now US)✦ </font> </i></b><br>\r\n<center><img src=\"https://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_jpg/pLhvdZgejGSicEvduTWrmGibZXZVrqltibPZwDj7CqQlcxjKpyB9Mbial0gsibmrC1B6rZEXBbts5QRkonbSztUaeLA/640?wx_fmt=jpeg&amp;tp=webp&amp;wxfrom=5&amp;wx_lazy=1&amp;wx_co=1\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\"></center><br><br>\r\n<center>\r\n<img src=\"https://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_jpg/pLhvdZgejGSicEvduTWrmGibZXZVrqltibPicyvkk67empevIKvXpXP4pibvgZmywGOnXNCJ1fWLYAEbqmAs8B9UUJw/640?wx_fmt=jpeg&amp;tp=webp&amp;wxfrom=5&amp;wx_lazy=1&amp;wx_co=1\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\"></center><br>\r\n<font size=\"2\"><b><i>In the last seconds, it is as if everyone leaped off the mount, hold hands.The end approaches like approaching ground. Like honey is the sleep of just. (Orthros) </i></b><br>\r\n玻璃纤维、水性树脂、聚氨酯、混凝土、石膏、MDF、聚碳酸酯\r\n<br>2019</font><br><br><br>\r\n\r\n   <center><img src=\"https://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_jpg/pLhvdZgejGSicEvduTWrmGibZXZVrqltibPEASvlgo7Y6laJoMx77a5GeXbyzpFVXeKN9OnWnmAs81tIFzicUoJgkQ/640?wx_fmt=jpeg&amp;tp=webp&amp;wxfrom=5&amp;wx_lazy=1&amp;wx_co=1\" alt=\"Girl in a jacket\" width=\"400\" height=\"550\"></center><br> \r\n   <font align=\"left\" size=\"2\"><b><i>Thus, on any day, at any hour of any day, the stretch of sky left me wild and breathless. If the world ends now we are free, not a bee moved up from your spine inside. (Geryon) </i></b><br>\r\n玻璃纤维、水性树脂\r\n<br>2019</font><br><br><br>\r\n\r\n<center>\r\n<img src=\"https://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_gif/pLhvdZgejGSicEvduTWrmGibZXZVrqltibPEI1IiajMrEwP1bicQOVvyblpotBfDpZzT2UEqFJYAqRrrKaicbAMepZpw/640?wx_fmt=gif&amp;tp=webp&amp;wxfrom=5&amp;wx_lazy=1\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\"></center><br>\r\n<font align=\"left\" size=\"2\"><b><i>Supposed old old age might show grow old to show what it meant the soul is made of wind instead of warm red liquid (Crossing River Styx) </i></b><br>\r\n冷铸青铜<br>2019</font><br><br><br>\r\n\r\n<center><img src=\"https://mmbiz.qpic.cn/mmbiz_jpg/pLhvdZgejGSicEvduTWrmGibZXZVrqltibPOy2SPMMVbFcO3FFiadPhDyrE2umOpVmyulJ8wfFP3aVHetfIn63HhfA/640?wx_fmt=jpeg&amp;tp=webp&amp;wxfrom=5&amp;wx_lazy=1&amp;wx_co=1\" alt=\"Girl in a jacket\" width=\"400\" height=\"550\